title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 4900.6 - Information not available
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 4900.6 - Information not available

State Regulations

Notwithstanding any other provision in this Part, this
section shall not apply to information that is: (a) specifically exempted by
statute; (b) maintained for the
regulation of commercial enterprise, including trade secrets, which if openly
disclosed would permit an unfair advantage to competitors of the subject
enterprise; (c) if disclosed, an
unwarranted invasion of personal privacy within the standards of this

Part; (d) compiled for law
enforcement purposes and which, if disclosed, would: (1)
interfere with law enforcement
investigations or judicial proceedings; (2)
deprive a person of a right to a fair
trial or impartial adjudication; (3)
identify a confidential source or
disclose confidential information relating to a criminal investigation; or
(4)
reveal criminal
investigative techniques or procedures, except routine techniques and
procedures; (e) dangerous
to the life or safety of any person, if disclosed; (f) inter-agency or intra-agency materials
that are not: (1)
statistical or factual
tabulations or data; (2)
instructions to staff that affect the public; or
(3)
final agency policy or
determinations; (g) examination questions or answere which are requested prior to the final
administration of such questions; (h) information which, if disclosed, would
impair present or imminent contract awards or collective bargaining
negotiations. Notes
